76561197961214179,Recommended,404530,34963954,Posted: 14 September,all,Jack Madadov,"I was hooked instantly. There's so much to do.  Great value for your entertainment dollar.Update 1: (60+ hours)This game is spectacular. It has everything.  You can build cities via the mapmode.  The cities are functional in the sense that it is the world you are playing.  Building placement is about what works best for you.The economic design is solid.  Vanilla settings permit you a healthy set of options in the beginning.  Complete a few early missions to boost your progress.  You can make an impact on the game if you have a focus.Earn some money.  Build some things.  Balance the RICO and perk buildings. Use the money to do more.  Build bigger.  You could spend all day making the ultimate apartment building.  Or, you could create a meat grinder of enemy AI vs your AI.  Turn the local area into a pot marked hellscape.  FUN!Combat.  This game is about management.  You are managing simple soldiers fighting simple enemies.  They won't get all ""tactical"" on you and execute complicated maneuvers.  Enemies charge and shoot until you or they are dead.  Simple.  Yet, the management aspect of the game is where the strategy lies.  Want to conquer a base?  Sure, you can be all stealthy and tactical if you want to play John Wayne and take the world on by yourself.  But... it is more fun, IMO, to surround the enemy base with a few of your own bases, fully fortified.  Use some rockets to shell their compound while your AI minions fight them.  Numbers.  Have two bases or more.  Maybe three or four for those big bases populated with missile soldiers.While they do that, go jack a car.  Get the missile spawning perk.  Charge the base and strafe it with missiles.  I do this for hours, laughing maniacally.  I don't know if they have a name for what's wrong with me."
