t in my game, i bought a gun, and i went on a killing spree in the buildings next to the gun store. I shot down a full business building and made about 5k with all the money the people dropped. Even though the guns don't feel nice and the way npc's die is just laughable, its actually kind of fun to go around and f*cking sh*t upThe car-play is also pretty good. I enjoyed the controls the game has for the cars. It feels right, fast and fun. You can't run people over though... they just kinda float over your car, and it's kind of disappointingThe core idea of the game is great. It's just about giving the game and the dev more time to improve his work, and this will be a great game. It just needs to work in its graphics and some other small things.I think i'm being too harsh on a one-man made game that has been out for about a week. Maybe i should play a little bit more and then make my review, but i honestly don't like how the game feels and plays. Even though my review is negative and i've listed a nice amount of not-so-good things, i kinda do recommend this game. The only thing i think it should do, its to change it's aesthetics. People like the gameplay and i think i could enjoy it too if i got a little bit deeper, but its mostly the graphics what's making this game a bit of a pain for me. I say you should give it a try, buy it. It's not that expensive and if you can ignore the graphics, you might be in for a great time."
