76561197977820099,Not Recommended,404530,34963375,Posted: 14 September,all,Lizzard,"I feel bad being the first negative review and this game doesn’t really deserve a full thumbs down… but it doesn’t really deserve an entirely positive rating. There’s one simple reason for this - “Broke Protocol”.The above-mentioned game features many of the core elements as this one, minus the city-building portion. I only use it as a comparison because it’s entirely free to play vs. the $7 tag this game has.When you take the difference between the two games, what you essentially get is a $7 voxel city building game, minus the management aspects of Sim City, for your money with this purchase. And even though $7 isn’t much, it’s hard to really justify spending that much on a game that only has one difference from a free to play game of the same genre.Pros: ability to create your own city; ability to play in the world of your city, interact with residents, purchase land, etc.; freedom to act however you like in said city - rob a bank, build a house, own a business, blow holes in office buildings, etc.Cons: The destruction advertised feels more like accidentally hitting the delete key when you build something in Minecraft - the blocks vanish and that’s about it; cars don’t respond to any damage and just keep driving like nothing happened (minus falling in a pothole your grenade created); driving is ultra-unrealistic and the controls feel more like playing a 3d game of PacMan, than driving an actual car; cars also lack anything but the most basic of physics relating to being hit by other cars, other than swerving a bit - don’t expect any pin maneuvers or noteworthy crashes; gun fire sounds, looks and feels more like shooting a pellet gun; targets are ridiculously hard to hit, as people just go flailing around wildly when you shoot and they take an insane amount of damage to kill; AI police are also a special level of stupid, failing to go looking for you inside of buildings, even if you never leave the scene of the crime.Even for an EA game, the list of cons combined with the lack of original features of similar games so far, leaves this game coming up short of what you’d probably expect.."
